-- Skoda Auto Stops Saturday Production Over Pay Dispute, CTK Says
-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 2012-04-04T10:27:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/skoda-auto-stops-saturday-production-over-pay-dispute-ctk-says.html
Skoda Auto AS, the Czech unit of
 Volkswagen AG (VOW) , will stop Saturday production after the company
failed to reach a new agreement with labor unions,  CTK  newswire
reported, citing union leader Jaroslav Povsik.  Skoda offered a 4.3 percent pay increase, while the unions
want 6 percent, the newswire said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
 placa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  